5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to public assistance; to require the
10 Department of Human Resources to request a waiver to exclude
11 candy and soda from the definition of "eligible foods" for
12 purposes of SNAP benefits; to require the department to
13 prohibit the purchase of candy and soda with SNAP benefits if
14 the waiver is granted; to require the Department of Revenue to
15 coordinate implementation of the waiver and provide for the
16 duties of the department; and to provide for the resubmission
17 of the request, if the request is denied; and to prohibit
18 penalties for certain retailers for accidental noncompliance,
19 with exceptions.
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
21 Section 1. (a) For the purposes of this section, the
22 following terms have the following meanings:
23 (1) CANDY. Food products that list sugar, cane sugar,
24 corn syrup, or high fructose corn syrup as a primary
25 ingredient. The term includes any confectionery products
26 primarily composed of sugar or sweeteners and intended for
27 consumption as candy, including, but not limited to, chocolate
28 bars, non-chocolate candy, chewing gum, and similar products.
Page 1

bars, non-chocolate candy, chewing gum, and similar products.
SB57 Engrossed
29 The term does not include any baked goods, prepared desserts,
30 bakery items, baking mixes, cooking ingredients, dessert
31 toppings, frostings, jellies, jams, marshmallows, hot cocoa
32 mix, powdered drink mixes, or other foods intended primarily
33 for cooking, baking, or meal preparation.
34 (2) DEPARTMENT. The Alabama Department of Human
35 Resources.
36 (3) SNAP BENEFIT. A financial benefit, coupon, or
37 privilege available under the federal Supplemental Nutrition
38 Assistance Program, 7 U.S.C. Chapter 51.
39 (4) SODA. Beverages that list, as the first two
40 ingredients, any combination of: (i) carbonated water; and
41 (ii) sugar, cane sugar, corn syrup, or high fructose corn
42 syrup. The term does not include any beverages that contain
43 low or non-caloric sweeteners.
44 (5) USDA FOOD AND NUTRITION SERVICE. The United States
45 Department of Agriculture Food and Nutrition Service.
46 (b) The commissioner of the department shall request a
47 waiver from the USDA Food and Nutrition Service to authorize
48 the department to exclude candy and soda from the definition
49 of "eligible foods" under 7 C.F.R. § 271.2.
50 (c)(1) If the waiver described in subsection (b) is
51 approved by the USDA Food and Nutrition Service, the
52 department shall prohibit the use of SNAP benefits for the
53 purchase of candy and soda, provided that retailers must be
54 provided at least one month's notice before the waiver may
55 become effective. The Department of Revenue, in consultation
56 with the department, shall provide notice of the effective
Page 2

with the department, shall provide notice of the effective
SB57 Engrossed
57 date of the waiver to SNAP-authorized retailers.
58 (2) The Department of Revenue shall coordinate with
59 SNAP-authorized retailers to implement the approved waiver.
60 The Alabama Department of Revenue shall work directly with
61 retailers to:
62 a. Identify items included and excluded under the
63 waiver; and
64 b. Provide guidance on SNAP-eligible and
65 SNAP-ineligible purchases. The guidance shall include, but not
66 be limited to, product identification on existing universal
67 product codes or other standard point-of-sale identifiers used
68 by retailers.
69 (3) The Department of Revenue shall offer technical
70 assistance, training, and any other necessary resources to
71 support retailers in compliance with the waiver and minimize
72 disruption to retail operations.
73 (d) If the waiver described in subsection (b) is
74 denied, the commissioner shall resubmit the request for a
75 waiver to the USDA Food and Nutrition Service annually until
76 approval is granted.
77 (e) If the waiver described in subsection (b) is
78 approved, no retailer may be subject to any fine, penalty, or
79 other punishment for the accidental acceptance of SNAP
80 benefits for the purchase of candy or soda, unless the
81 retailer has more than three accidental acceptances during one
82 fiscal year.
83 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
84 1, 2026.
